WEBVTT

00:04.204 --> 00:06.639
WOMAN (over P.A.): Dr. Esterman
to Radiology, Dr. Mark Esterman

00:06.705 --> 00:08.208
to Radiology.

00:08.274 --> 00:10.276
(phone ringing)

00:12.645 --> 00:14.114
Hello.

00:14.180 --> 00:15.548
David, hi. It's me.

00:16.850 --> 00:18.785
What's up? You okay?

00:18.852 --> 00:21.588
Noah's hurt. I'm calling you
from the emergency room.

00:21.654 --> 00:23.757
What's going... what's going on?

00:23.823 --> 00:26.126
It's Donna.
Noah's in the hospital.

00:26.192 --> 00:27.260
Is that Camille?

00:27.327 --> 00:29.362
Yeah. What's going on with Noah?

00:29.429 --> 00:32.098
Well, I ignored his calls
like you told me to do,

00:32.165 --> 00:34.234
and I guess he got drunk
and he broke in,

00:34.300 --> 00:35.735
and we all thought
he was a burglar, and...

00:35.802 --> 00:38.171
-and Matt went after him.
-You're kidding.

00:38.238 --> 00:40.039
So far, he has a concussion
and some bruised ribs.

00:40.106 --> 00:41.508
We're waiting for some tests,
but if they're clear,

00:41.574 --> 00:43.209
I'm just gonna take him
back to my place.

00:43.276 --> 00:46.246
No, Donna, if the guy
broke into your house

00:46.312 --> 00:49.382
'cause he couldn't get you on
the phone, you need some space.

00:49.449 --> 00:51.351
David, I don't need
your second-guessing right now.

00:51.418 --> 00:53.253
I just called
because you're his roommate.

00:53.319 --> 00:54.788
I thought you might
worry about him.

00:54.854 --> 00:57.757
Uh, I'll... I got to go.

00:57.824 --> 01:00.226
-(dial tone drones)
-(groans)

01:00.293 --> 01:01.261
(beep)

01:01.327 --> 01:02.662
The CAT scan came back fine.

01:02.729 --> 01:03.797
No cranial bleeding.

01:03.863 --> 01:06.299
He may experience some nausea

01:06.366 --> 01:07.700
over the next eight hours,

01:07.767 --> 01:08.835
and breathing won't tickle.

01:08.902 --> 01:10.470
Just keep an eye on him.

01:10.537 --> 01:12.172
Thanks.

01:14.340 --> 01:16.109
DONNA:
I, uh, was just calling David.

01:16.176 --> 01:18.278
I told him we'll be taking care
of Noah for a few days.

01:18.344 --> 01:19.446
We are?

01:19.512 --> 01:21.347
Mm-hmm.

01:21.414 --> 01:24.751
Okay, uh, I'm gonna
go get the car.

01:24.818 --> 01:27.787
(quietly):
Okay.

01:27.854 --> 01:30.356
Matt feels... awful.

01:30.423 --> 01:32.091
Well, he shouldn't.

01:32.158 --> 01:34.394
I guess you're right.

01:34.461 --> 01:37.764
Look, I know on principle you
could do without Noah around.

01:37.831 --> 01:39.799
Right again.

01:39.866 --> 01:41.267
But he needs a friend.

01:41.334 --> 01:44.137
How are you guys supposed
to get past things

01:44.204 --> 01:45.205
if he is sleeping

01:45.271 --> 01:46.406
on our couch?

01:46.473 --> 01:48.374
Kel, David already
gave me the lecture,

01:48.441 --> 01:49.776
and I appreciate your concern,

01:49.843 --> 01:52.545
but no one has anything
to worry about, especially me.

01:52.612 --> 01:54.180
All right.

01:54.247 --> 01:56.249
I'll hold you to that.

01:56.316 --> 01:58.518
I'll hold myself to that.
Thanks.

